source: alpha(t) = ifElse( t <= tC, ( t - tHist ) / ( tC - tHist ), 1.0 )

description:
Calculates the allowances of each country at each year so that they converge to their fair share.

qBar(i,t) = E(t) * ((alpha(t)*FS(i,t)) + (1- alpha(t))*GS(i))

qBar(i,t) = ifElse( allocation_rule == 0, E(t) * ( (alpha(t)*FS(i,t)) + (1- alpha(t))*GS(i) ), ifElse( allocation_rule == 2,  E(t) * ( (alpha(t)*GDPS(i,t)) + (1- alpha(t))*GS(i)), 666 ) )
name: qBar
source: qBar(i,t) = ifElse( allocation_rule == 0, E(t) * ( (alpha(t)*FS(i,t)) + (1- alpha(t))*GS(i) ), ifElse( allocation_rule == 2,  E(t) * ( (alpha(t)*GDPS(i,t)) + (1- alpha(t))*GS(i)), E(t) * FS(i,t) - (debt( i, t + 1 ) - debt( i, t )) ) )

abat( i, t ) = getcolumn( qBAU, i, t ) - qBar( i, t )
